[6] Chila - India (Karnataka)
Date: Thu 5 Apr 2012
Source: Daily News and Analysis (DNA) [edited]
http://www.dnaindia.com/health/report_mysore-reports-34-cholera-cases_1671799


If you are planning to visit Mysore, ensure that you carry safe drinking water and stick to eating homemade food. The city has reported 34 cases of cholera, said Mysore City Corporation officials on Wed 4 Apr 2012. The Epidemic Hospital is treating the patients.

Health officer Dr Nagaraj said cases have been reported from Metagalli, Kumbarakoppal to Kuvempunagar to Gangotri Layout. He attributed the outbreak of cholera to the poor quality of water supplied in hotels.

